---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Some things about me">
<main class="flex flex-col items-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <div class="mt-10 space-y-10">
    <h1 class="">About Me</h1>
    <p>Hey I'm Luke. I love to build. Right now I'm working on <a href="https://songkeeper.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="fancy-link">Songkeeper</a>, a music production management platform for tracking sessions, collaborators, splits, and releases.</p>

    <p>I have a mechanical engineering degree from Queen's University and spent a decade in the music industry as a <a href="https://lukeroes.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="fancy-link">producer, artist, and audio engineer</a>. I'm a self-taught developer and my current stack is TypeScript across the board — React (TanStack Start), Node.js (Hono, tRPC), PostgreSQL (Drizzle), and iOS (SwiftUI).</p>

    <p>Outside of code I still love to <a href="https://lukeroes.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="fancy-link">make music</a>, <a href="/recipes/sourdough" class="fancy-link">bake bread</a>, and run.</p>

    The site is built with Astro (+ React) and is <a href="https://github.com/lukemelnik/lukemelnik.co" class="fancy-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">open source</a>.
  </div>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
